<p>In my app, i have a profile View which has image, name, email etc that can be updated to the server using an API.</p>  <p>When i am trying to do so from web tool that developers has given me to test the api it works fine but i am doing this from iOS it fails all the time. Here's the how the request looks like in chrome.</p>  <p>Request Header :</p>  <pre><code>Accept:text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,*/*;q=0.8 Accept-Encoding:gzip, deflate Accept-Language:en-US,en;q=0.8 Cache-Control:max-age=0 Connection:keep-alive Content-Length:1239531 Content-Type:multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundarywuhZIoB4dE0J7FIm Host:IP:PORT Origin:http://IP:PORT Referer:http://IP:PORT/WebSocketChat/upload.html Upgrade-Insecure-Requests:1 User-Agent:Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_10_5) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/45.0.2454.85 Safari/537.36 </code></pre>  <p>and the Request Payload is this :</p>  <pre><code>------WebKitFormBoundarywuhZIoB4dE0J7FIm Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="thumb_DSC_0074_Edit_1024.png" Content-Type: image/png   ------WebKitFormBoundarywuhZIoB4dE0J7FIm Content-Disposition: form-data; name="firstname"  ABC ------WebKitFormBoundarywuhZIoB4dE0J7FIm Content-Disposition: form-data; name="lastname"  REWDS ------WebKitFormBoundarywuhZIoB4dE0J7FIm Content-Disposition: form-data; name="usermobile"  628292020 ------WebKitFormBoundarywuhZIoB4dE0J7FIm Content-Disposition: form-data; name="userid"  16 ------WebKitFormBoundarywuhZIoB4dE0J7FIm-- </code></pre>  <p>What should be the request like from iOS Swift 2.0?</p>  <p>What i have tried so far is :</p>  <pre><code>func updateProfile(postData:NSString,callback:(NSDictionary,String?) -&gt; Void) {         let url = NSURL(string: (baseURL+updateProfileURL))          let postRequest = NSMutableURLRequest(URL: url!)         postRequest.HTTPMethod = "POST"           let boundary = "*****"         postRequest.HTTPMethod = "POST"         postRequest.setValue("multipart/form-data; boundary=\(boundary)", forHTTPHeaderField: "Content-Type")         postRequest.setValue("image.png", forHTTPHeaderField: "uploaded_file")         postRequest.setValue("Keep-Alive", forHTTPHeaderField: "Connection")         postRequest.setValue("multipart/form-data", forHTTPHeaderField: "ENCTYPE")          let body : NSMutableData = NSMutableData()         body.appendString("--\(boundary)\r\n")         body.appendString("Content-Disposition: form-data;     name='uploaded_file';filename='image.png'\r\n")         body.appendString("Content-Type: \"application/octet-     stream\"\r\n\r\n")         let data = postData.dataUsingEncoding(NSUTF8StringEncoding)         body.appendData(data!)         body.appendString("\r\n")         body.appendString("--\(boundary)\r\n")          postRequest.HTTPBody = body           let postSession = NSURLSession.sharedSession().dataTaskWithRequest(postRequest, completionHandler: {data, response, error -&gt; Void in             let result = NSString(data: data!, encoding: NSUTF8StringEncoding)             print(result)             do {                 let jsonData = try NSJSONSerialization.JSONObjectWithData(data!, options: .MutableContainers) as! NSDictionary                 callback(jsonData, nil)             }             catch {                 print("Some Error")             }          })          postSession.resume()      } </code></pre>